        <abstract> 
<p>Encloses some notes on <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> [2d ed.]. Discusses CD’s contention [p. 130] that natural selection could not act to increase altruistic behaviour in man; considers that the benefits conferred upon a person exhibiting such virtues would outweigh the threat to survival that such behaviour would pose.</p> 
        </abstract>
